txt.en: A moan flows across the wind as more of the Barrow-downs awakes.
The gauntlet has begun. All you can do now is hope to survive....
You have all been defeated or left the spire.
The wind chills as the inhabitants of the Barrow-downs grow in power.
The inhabitants of the Barrow-downs do not take kindly to visitors.
'You should not have come here, and now you shall pay for your transgressions. The Dead do not forgive.'
A shade has appeared within the Barrow-downs. Speak with him to discover why he is here.
The Barrow-downs have unleashed their fury. Hold your position for as long as you can possibly stand.
The battle above must not have started in order to use this exit.
Survive for as long as possible
Do not be defeated or leave the spire
'This place will soon be your grave too....'
